      "raw_text": "The Northern Pacific railway officials\nserved notice on the city commissioners\nthis morning that the city would DC\nheld responsible for any damage that\nmay result from deepening the cut\nupder the railroad tracks on Wash\nineton street.\n\n\nThis work is being done by the Spo-\nkane Traction company, which in turn,\nhas put up a $4,000 bond guaranteeing\nthe city against damage in connection\nwith the deepening of the cut.\n\n\nThe traction company is seeking TO\nhase a clear way of Is feet under the\nNorthern Pacific tracks. Pending an in\nvestigation by the city engineer and\nthe board of public works, the work\n'wss checked this morning."
